This paper is about the evaluation of dialogue systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP research. Additionally, since dialogue systems involve artificial intelligence (AI), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. Human-computer interaction (cs.HC) is another possible sub-category, as the evaluation of dialogue systems often involves human participants. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant, as dialogue systems often involve retrieving information from a database or knowledge base. Finally, machine learning (cs.LG) is a possible sub-category, as many dialogue systems use machine learning techniques for natural language understanding and generation.
